            <h3 data-uuid="2bfe8748390b42ae91f31f49acaf6728">Part 2: Write an Analytical Essay</h3>
            <h6 data-uuid="cc32c1ea22eb4b88941192d2db56e8ab">Historical Context</h6>
            <p data-uuid="cc41a83b67d9471a81f8627037863c17">Inequality and corruption were facts of life during the Gilded Age. The Progressive movement was the result of reform-minded individuals joining together to expand rights, improve working conditions, uncover corruption, fight discrimination, and reform the political system.</p>
            <h6 data-uuid="822cbe40ae2745ed96d2ca4649728817">Task</h6>
            <p data-uuid="1466d59955f244dea25cdb1bcc02bf60">The Gilded Age was a time of great injustice in American society. Write
                an essay that explains at least three of the major societal issues in need of
                reform.</p>
            <p data-uuid="662b11ab9f2446f1ab40035d144b41d1">Complete the following steps as you plan and compose your essay.</p>
        </section>
        <ol data-uuid="48ae2a5d0b674396b577aeac8c9ef3f9">
            <li data-uuid="a03228e588504669aa77de350eb5f78e">Review your notes and sources before you start writing.</li>
            <li data-uuid="72cd2208eb2b4c48bdaa069d2dd8d286">Use at least <i>three</i> of the sources in Part 1, and develop the topic with relevant, well-chosen text or visual evidence from the documents.</li>
            <li data-uuid="00366e9b0cef439b94a3ac19ad310bad">Cite specific text or visual evidence from each of the sources in your response.</li>
            <li data-uuid="6e6ff7d3c1b0437188da8f44d5f406ce">Plan your essay so that it includes an introduction, several body paragraphs, and a concluding paragraph.</li>
            <li data-uuid="9b47e9bc678d4d1faad71862aaac3268">Organize your essay in a clear and logical way that links evidence and important details to your main topic.</li>
            <li data-uuid="28f60bdd84a6470f96fd684f217336c7">Write a conclusion that sums up your ideas and supports the information you present.</li>
        </ol>
